<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-10-04T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-10-04T19:00:00-05:00" n="299" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d299">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">501.<gloss target="#t_BC1">BC</gloss>
                                Indonesia/10–548: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Batavia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Livengood</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                    <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                                    <lb/>
                                    <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                                    </gloss>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Batavia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-10-05T08:00:00+08:00">October 5, 1948—8 a. m.</date>–<date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-10-05T13:00:00+08:00">1 p. m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>874[–879]. <gloss target="#t_Gocus1">Gocus</gloss> 402. <gloss target="#t_NethDel1">NethDel</gloss> delivered <gloss target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss> 12 midnight October 4 following
                                confidential letter dated Batavia October 5 addressed Cochran.</p>
                            <p>[Here follows text of letter with enclosures, quoted in telegrams
                                874–879, October 5, <gloss target="#t_Gocus1">Gocus</gloss> 402,
                                none printed. For text as finally submitted on October 14, see
                                    <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>, <hi rend="italic">3rd yr.,
                                    Suppl</hi>. (Dec), page 169. See also telegram 913, October 14,
                                10 p. m., <gloss target="#t_Gocus1">Gocus</gloss> 411, <ref target="#pg_418">page 418</ref>.]</p>
                            <p>Signed Cochran.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Livengood</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>